() Tj
T*
(* `User`: email-based authentication model.) Tj
T*
(* `CapabilityProfile`: company capabilities, NAICS codes, certifications, past performance,) Tj
T*
(contact data, matchmaking tags, and OCR text.) Tj
T*
(* `AdditionalEmail`: extra customer email addresses.) Tj
T*
(* `MailboxConnection`: Gmail/Outlook OAuth connection metadata and signed tokens.) Tj
T*
(* `Contract`: opportunity data including source, portal, title, summary, agency, NAICS,) Tj
T*
(deadline, link, status, and partner.) Tj
T*
(* `UserContractProgress`: per-user pursuit status, workflow status, relationship label, and) Tj
T*
(notes.) Tj
T*
(* `DismissedContract`: opportunities hidden by a user.) Tj
T*
(* `ContractNotification`: deadline, status, progress, and workflow notifications.) Tj
T*
(* `EmailIngestionMessage`: mailbox messages processed during sync.) Tj
T*
(* `MailboxContract`: relationships between mailbox messages and contract records.) Tj
T*
(* `UserMatchmakingCache`: cached AI/rule-based match results for a user.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Major Workflows) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Account and Profile Workflow) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. User creates an account or logs in.) Tj
T*
(2. User creates or edits a capability profile.) Tj
T*
(3. User may upload a capability statement document for OCR extraction.) Tj
T*
(4. User selects NAICS codes and matchmaking preferences.) Tj
T*
(5. Profile data becomes available for contract matching and RFP generation.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Opportunity Discovery Workflow) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. Procurement opportunities are added through SAM.gov ingestion or existing data.) Tj
T*
(2. Authenticated users can browse opportunities.) Tj
T*
(3. Users can filter and search by NAICS, agency, status, partner, and keywords.) Tj
T*
(4. Users can open contract detail pages for richer review.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Matchmaking Workflow) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. The backend reads the user's capability profile.) Tj
T*
(2. The backend compares profile fields, NAICS codes, keywords, certifications, timeline) Tj
T*
(data, and optional embeddings against visible contracts.) Tj
T*
(3. The system returns match scores, percentages, strongest alignment, weak alignment, and) Tj
T*
(match reasons.) Tj
T*
(4. Results are cached for reuse until the user refreshes matches.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Contract Management Workflow) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. User marks progress for a contract.) Tj
T*
(2. User updates workflow stage and relationship label.) Tj
T*
(3. User adds notes.) Tj
T*
(4. User can dismiss opportunities that are not relevant.) Tj
T*
ET
endstream
endobj
